{"about_the_game":"T-Minus 30 is a fast-paced, single-player city builder where you plan a city and assemble a space fleet to escape a dying Earth.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/1._Intro.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>You must scavenge a post-apocalyptic environment to build infrastructure, grow crops, generate power, and build rockets to save as many people as you can. All within 30 minutes of play.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/2._30_Minutes.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>You start your new settlement with the intention of turning post-apocalyptic land into working rocketry.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/3._Start_from_Nothing.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>So, you start by digging Wells which produce and propagate Water.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/4._Water.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>Then you create Tilled Earth, which receives that Water and becomes Farmland, which in turn produces Food.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/5._Till.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>You can build up your infrastructure to support solar farms and hydroponics labs to stock sleek generational ships that each rescue thousands of evacuees.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/6._Infrastructure.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>Or, you can remain low-tech and brute force your population off the Earth by building massive numbers of 1960s era rocketry.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/7._Low_Tech.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>And, that's T-Minus 30. A timeboxed city builder that focuses on resource propagation, exploration, and saving as much of humanity as you can before the Earth explodes.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1371750/extras/8._Rockets.gif?t=1683806843\" /><br><br>Mind you, however you play, you can't save everyone, and people will still end up dead.<br><br>But that's life.<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Explore abandoned ruins of a once-bustling civilization.<br></li><li> Mine skyscrapers and junkyards to reclaim plastics and metals.<br></li><li> Explore procedurally generated landscapes, from small, arid maps with scarce resources to large, forested maps replete with ancient ruins.<br></li><li> Create the infrastructure to convey energy, water, and other resources to your ever-expanding base of operations.<br></li><li> Save as many souls as you can before the world ends in 30 minutes!</li></ul>","achievements":{"highlighted":[{"name":"Sensible","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1371750/30689c45341792493b1b7310824ea1bbe7cb41d9.jpg"},{"name":"Blast Off!","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1371750/d39b0b75f7a51ea0b45ece307bcc39dc1bffd573.jpg"},{"name":"Rocket!","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1371750/4dc42ec23c8e3d17366c2d0e5ac7fd553d9d7797.jpg"},{"name":"Rocket Meister","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1371750/45e56b8778c574db03ada6999af75ccbb5101457.jpg"},{"name":"Green Finger","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1371750/fe617b8e769056685e87a6036399a7e8a04fc2aa.jpg"},{"name":"Carbon Capture","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1371750/e7514d9436d43dd2ca329825c8b33fca745687a4.jpg"},{"name":"Scavenger","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/stea